==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mineralizer
<hw>Min"er*al*i`zer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An element
which is combined with a metal, thus forming an ore. <as>Thus, in
galena, or lead ore, sulphur is a <ex>mineralizer</ex>; in hematite,
oxygen is a <ex>mineralizer</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mineralogical</ent>⟦br⟧
